-- Carbon black producer Orion files for U.S. IPO
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 05:57PM EDT
-- None



July 14 (Reuters) - Carbon black producer Orion Engineered Carbons S.A. filed for a U.S. IPO that could raise about $432 million.

Private equity investors Triton Capital and Rhone Group each own 41.83 percent of the company through Kinove Holdings, the filing said. (http://1.usa.gov/1nzBouC) Kinove, which own 89.69 percent of Orion, will sell 18 million common shares, expected to be priced $21 to $24 each. Morgan Stanley and Goldman, Sachs & Co are the lead underwriters of the offering, the Luxembourg-based company told the U.S Securities and Exchange Commission.